hackathon-description-text: Open to beginners! Current college students are invited for Syracuse University's first 24 hour hackathon starting at 11:30AM on Saturday, April 21st. Create anything from applications to websites. Work with a team or solo, and present your project the next day for the chance to win cool prizes!

hackathon-prizes.prize-content: 1st Choice of Drone, Echo Dot, Hard Drive
2nd Choice of Drone, Echo Dot, Hard Drive
3rd Choice of Drone, Echo Dot, Hard Drive

hackathon-prizes.prize-title: Best Education, Diversity or Inclusion Hack

hackathon-location-google-maps: https://maps.google.com/?q=107 College Pl, Syracuse, NY 13210, USA

hackathon-judging-criteria.judging-criterion: How high-tech/technically intricate is your project?
How organized/aesthetically pleasing is your project?
How does your project stand out next to others'?

hackathon-description-header: 24-hour event to build cool and innovative applications, websites, and hardware projects
